Macro Economics Intelligence Platform

Breadlaunchers

Macro Intel is an AI-driven market intelligence platform designed to eliminate the information overload faced by asset managers. By replacing fragmented, manual monitoring with a unified "Macro Risk Radar," the solution tracks global developments and identifies when themes shift from emerging to critical.
The platform connects disparate events—such as a semiconductor shortage in Asia—to specific portfolio impacts like US tech valuations, providing immediate context across asset classes. It maintains a searchable "Institutional Memory" that preserves past discussions and news history, ensuring that team insights are never lost. To navigate the volume of data, an intuitive dashboard allows users to deep-dive into source articles while receiving real-time AI summaries.
Crucially, the solution addresses the problem of "analysis paralysis" by providing a "Full Risk Analysis" for every is feature predicts specific outcomes, such as how a "Global Inflation Pivot" might trigger a rate hike, and suggests concrete mitigation strategies like capital reallocation. By moving from reactive reporting to proactive forecasting, Macro Intel ensures that critical indicators are never overlooked, directly enhancing institutional risk management.

